    name: { en: 'Stuffed Lamb Tomatoes', ro: 'Rosii umplute cu miel', ru: 'Фаршированные помидоры с бараниной', es: 'Tomates rellenos con cordero' },
    category: 'Lamb',
    area: 'Greek',
    instructions: { en: 'Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Slice the tops off the tomatoes and reserve. Scoop out most of the pulp with a teaspoon, being careful not to break the skin. Finely chop the pulp, and keep any juices. Sprinkle the insides of the tomatoes with a little sugar to take away the acidity, then place them on a baking tray.\n\nHeat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan, add the onion and garlic, then gently cook for about 10 mins until soft but not coloured. Add the lamb, cinnamon and tomato purée, turn up the heat, then fry until the meat is browned. Add the tomato pulp and juice, the rice and the stock. Season generously. Bring to the boil, then simmer for 15 mins or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed. Set aside to cool a little, then stir in the herbs.\n\nStuff the tomatoes up to the brim, top tomatoes with their lids, drizzle with 2 tbsp more olive oil, sprinkle 3 tbsp water into the tray, then bake for 35 mins. Serve with salad and crusty bread, hot or cold.', ro: 'Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Feliaza the tops off the tomatoes and reserve. Scoop out most of the pulp with a teaspoon, being careful not to break the skin. Toaca marunt the pulp, and keep any juices. Sprinkle the insides of the tomatoes with a little sugar to take away the acidity, then punem on a baking tray.\n\nHeat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan, adauga onion and garlic, then gently gateste about 10 mins until soft but not coloured. Adauga lamb, cinnamon and tomato purée, turn up the heat, then fry until the meat is browned. Adauga tomato pulp and juice, the rice and the stock. Season generously. Adu la fierbere, then fierbe la foc mic 15 mins or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed. Pune deoparte to cool a little, then amesteca herbs.\n\nUmple tomatoes up to the brim, top tomatoes with their lids, drizzle with 2 tbsp more olive oil, sprinkle 3 tbsp water into the tray, then coace 35 mins. Servesteste cu salad and crusty bread, hot or cold.', ru: 'Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Нарежьте the tops off the tomatoes and reserve. Scoop out most of the pulp with a teaspoon, being careful not to break the skin. Мелко нарежьте the pulp, and keep any juices. Sprinkle the insides of the tomatoes with a little sugar to take away the acidity, then поместитеm on a baking tray.\n\nHeat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan, добавьте onion and garlic, then gently готовьте about 10 mins until soft but not coloured. Добавьте lamb, cinnamon and tomato purée, turn up the heat, then fry until the meat is browned. Добавьте tomato pulp and juice, the rice and the stock. Season generously. Доведите до кипения, then тушите 15 mins or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed. Отложите в сторону to cool a little, then вмешайте herbs.\n\nНафаршируйте tomatoes up to the brim, top tomatoes with their lids, drizzle with 2 tbsp more olive oil, sprinkle 3 tbsp water into the tray, then выпекайте 35 mins. Подавайте с salad and crusty bread, hot or cold.', es: 'Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Corte en rodajas the tops off the tomatoes and reserve. Scoop out most of the pulp with a teaspoon, being careful not to break the skin. Pique finamente the pulp, and keep any juices. Sprinkle the insides of the tomatoes with a little sugar to take away the acidity, then coloquem on a baking tray.\n\nHeat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan, anade onion and garlic, then gently cocine about 10 mins until soft but not coloured. Anade lamb, cinnamon and tomato purée, turn up the heat, then fry until the meat is browned. Anade tomato pulp and juice, the rice and the stock. Season generously. Lleve a ebullicion, then cocine a fuego lento 15 mins or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed. Reserve to cool a little, then incorpore herbs.\n\nRellene tomatoes up to the brim, top tomatoes with their lids, drizzle with 2 tbsp more olive oil, sprinkle 3 tbsp water into the tray, then hornee 35 mins. Sirva con salad and crusty bread, hot or cold.' },
